description:
In episode 915, Jack and Miles are joined by comedian Sara June to discuss McDonalds eggs, the culture wars over Palestine, vaccination badges on dating apps, a new Quincy Jones interview, a kidnapping being thwarted thanks to Law & Order: SVU, the exploding Goop candle, and more!

FOOTNOTES:

  1. TIL McDonald’s serves five different types of eggs, and one is superior to the rest
  2. The Associated Press terminates new staffer amid uproar over tweets about Israel and Palestinians, sparking backlash
  3. Pakistan's top diplomat makes anti-Semitic remark during CNN interview about Gaza conflict
  4. Major dating apps including Tinder, OkCupid adding vaccination badges to dating profiles
  5. THR Icon: Quincy Jones Reflects on Career, Michael Jackson and Why He Wouldn’t Work With Elvis
  6. An 11-Year-Old Girl Used Tactics She Learned From ‘Law & Order: SVU’ To Fight Off — And Help Nab — A Would-Be Kidnapper
  7. GWYNETH PALTROW Goop Sued ... YOUR 'VAGINA' CANDLE BLEW UP!!!
  8. Gwyneth Paltrow's Goop calls lawsuit over exploding vagina-scented candle 'frivolous'
  9. Experience: Gwyneth Paltrow’s vagina candle erupted in my front room 
  10. LISTEN: Mk.gee - cz [Official Music Video]
